reports_03_11_2020 <-   read_csv(url("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_daily_reports/03-11-2020.csv")) %>%
  rename(Country.Region = "Country/Region", Province.State = "Province/State")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `Province/State` = col_character(),

##   Deaths = col_double(),
##   Recovered = col_double(),

##   Longitude = col_double()
## )
head(reports_03_11_2020)

str(reports_03_11_2020)

##  $ Deaths        : num [1:216] 3046 827 354 60 48 ...

reports_03_11_2020 %>% 
  filter (Country.Region == "China") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Confirmed,  y = reorder(Province.State, Confirmed))) + 
    geom_point() +
    ggtitle("Confirmed cases for each State in China") +
    ylab("Country/Region") +
    xlab("Confirmed Cases")

reports_03_11_2020 %>% 
  filter (Country.Region == "US") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Confirmed,  y = reorder(Province.State, Confirmed))) + 
    geom_point() +
    ggtitle("Confirmed cases for each State in US") +
    ylab("Country/Region") +
    xlab("Confirmed Cases")

reports_03_11_2020 %>% 
  filter (Country.Region == "US") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Deaths,  y = reorder(Province.State, Deaths))) + 
    geom_point() +
    ggtitle("Death cases for each State in US") +
    ylab("Country/Region") +
    xlab("Confirmed Cases")

reports_03_11_2020 %>% 
  group_by(Country.Region) %>% 
  summarise(Deaths = sum(Deaths)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(Deaths))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
## # A tibble: 116 x 2
##    Country.Region Deaths
##    <chr>           <dbl>
##  1 China            3161
##  2 Italy             827
##  3 Iran              354
##  4 Korea, South       60
##  5 Spain              54
##  6 France             48
##  7 US                 36
##  8 Japan              15
##  9 United Kingdom      8
## 10 Cruise Ship         7
## # … with 106 more rows
reports_03_11_2020 %>%
  group_by(Country.Region) %>% 
  summarise(Confirmed = sum(Confirmed)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(Confirmed))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
## # A tibble: 116 x 2
##    Country.Region Confirmed
##    <chr>              <dbl>
##  1 China              80921
##  2 Italy              12462
##  3 Iran                9000
##  4 Korea, South        7755
##  5 France              2284
##  6 Spain               2277
##  7 Germany             1908
##  8 US                  1281
##  9 Cruise Ship          696
## 10 Switzerland          652
## # … with 106 more rows
reports_03_11_2020 %>% 
  group_by(Country.Region) %>% 
  summarise(Confirmed = sum(Confirmed)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(Confirmed)) %>% 
  slice(1:10) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Confirmed,  y = reorder(Country.Region, Confirmed))) + 
    geom_bar(stat = 'identity') +
    ggtitle("Coronavirus: Top ten most-affected countries Covid-19 ") +
    ylab("Country/Region") +
    xlab("Confirmed")
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)

reports_03_11_2020 %>% 
  group_by(Country.Region) %>% 
  summarise(Deaths = sum(Deaths)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(Deaths)) %>% 
  slice(1:10) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Deaths,  y = reorder(Country.Region, Deaths))) + 
    geom_bar(stat = 'identity') +
    ggtitle("The 10 countries with the most reported COV19-related deaths") +
    ylab("Country/Region") +
    xlab("Deaths")
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
